  <p>Digital radiology gives us the ability to see inside your pet's body quickly and accurately, helping us diagnose injuries, illnesses, and conditions that aren't visible during a physical exam.</p>

  <h2>When Is Radiology Recommended?</h2>
  <p>Your veterinarian may recommend X-rays for a number of reasons, including:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Suspected fractures or bone injuries</li>
    <li>Respiratory issues (coughing, difficulty breathing)</li>
    <li>Abdominal concerns (vomiting, bloating, loss of appetite)</li>
    <li>Heart or lung evaluation</li>
    <li>Foreign body ingestion</li>
    <li>Pre-surgical planning</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Benefits of Digital Radiology</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Faster results compared to traditional film</li>
    <li>Higher image quality for more accurate diagnoses</li>
    <li>Lower radiation exposure for your pet</li>
    <li>Images can be easily shared with specialists if needed</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Our in-house digital radiology equipment allows us to get answers fast and start treatment sooner. Contact us if your pet needs diagnostic imaging.</p>
</ServiceLayout>
